import numpy as np

def BasicPower(matrix, power):
    N = matrix.shape[0]
    temp = matrix.copy()
    temp_ = np.zeros((N, N))
    for i in range(0, power-1):
        temp_ = temp.copy()
        temp = np.zeros((N, N))
        for j in range(0, N):
            for k in range(0, N):
                for l in range(0, N):
                    temp[j][k] += temp_[j, l] * matrix[l, k]
    return temp

# print(BasicPower(C)  
%timeit BasicPower(np.array([[1,2],[2,1]]), 20)
